Male. Pronotum slightly narrower; lateral tooth in middle of pronotum smoother, not well defined. First four protarsomeres weakly dilated, with longer and thicker ventral setae. Abdominal sternite VIII (
Fig. 8
) and tergite VIII (
Fig. 9
) with weakly emarginate posterior margin. Aedeagus (
Fig. 10
) wide and short, gradually tapering towards apex; parameres wide, exceeding apex of aedeagus, slightly curved medially. Aedeagus laterally as in
Fig. 11
